<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SPRING VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The body of a woman was found Monday morning in Spring Valley, authorities 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
Two area residents found the body, which has not been identified, at the bottom 
of an embankment in the 9400 block of Edgewood Drive, a Sheriff's Department 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the San Diego County coroner's office said an autopsy had been 
performed, but he would not release any more information. 
</P>
<P>
The cause of death has not been determined, but the Metropolitan Homicide Task 
Force is monitoring the investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
