<LENGTH>
<P>
123 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN YSIDRO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A La Mirada man died early Monday after being stabbed in a San Ysidro parking 
lot, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Rubin Salido, 27, was declared dead at the UC San Diego Medical Center shortly 
after 2 a.m., according to police. 
</P>
<P>
Officers were sent at 12:30 a.m. to a gas station in the 300 block of East San 
Ysidro Boulevard after someone reported a stabbing there, the spokesman said. 
He said the officers found no one there but got another report of a stabbing 
near a fire station five minutes away. 
</P>
<P>
Officers found the wounded Salido near the station, at Palm and Twining 
avenues, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Investigators learned from witnesses that Salido and another man had been 
arguing before Salido was stabbed, the spokesman said. No one has been 
arrested. 
</P>
