<P>
Home Prices Still Rising: Despite a slowing economy, there is no end in sight 
for California's skyrocketing home prices, according to a Bank of America 
report. The median price of a single-family home in the state is expected to 
rise 24% this year to $205,000, compared to $165,602 in 1988, according to the 
bank's report. In Orange County and San Francisco, the median home price will 
break the $300,000 mark by the end of next year, and in Los Angeles it will top 
$250,000, according to the report. A slower economy and higher interest rates 
will cool the demand for housing somewhat in 1990, but the median price will 
still rise 7% to $220,000, the report said. 
