<HEADLINE>
<P>
TWO ESCAPEES HOMESICK AFTER DAY AT THE BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GRAND RAPIDS, Mich. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A day at the beach proved too taxing for two escaped inmates who called their 
jailer collect and asked if they could return, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Mark Allen Fox and Charles F. Rohn, both 19, were back at the Michigan 
Reformatory at Ionia on Monday, facing possible escape charges, Warden Pamela 
Withrow said. 
</P>
<P>
"They said they spent the day at the beach, they were a little scared and 
hungry," said state trooper Larry Medendorp of the pair's trip to an unknown 
lake beach. The two, along with a third inmate who remained at large Monday, 
escaped Sunday from the prison's minimum-security dormitory unit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
