<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRANSPAC CREWS AWAITING ADJUSTED RESULTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALMON LOCKABEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With the leaders arriving in the 2,225-mile Los Angeles-to-Honolulu Transpac 
yacht race, crews are awaiting adjusted results with handicap times taken into 
consideration. 
</P>
<P>
Although Silver Bullet was first to finish in the Class A fleet, her handicap 
lead was short-lived as Taxi Dancer, third to finish, saved time allowance and 
took over first in Class A and in fleet. 
</P>
<P>
As of the 8 a.m. Monday roll call, the Class C yacht Medicine Man, still 334 
miles from the finish at Diamond Head, has a chance to beat Taxi Dancer for the 
overall corrected time victory. The results depend largely on the wind. 
</P>
<P>
By late Monday, only 24 of the 46 starters had finished; final results may not 
be known before Wednesday. ALMON LOCKABEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
