<HEADLINE>
<P>
TWO PALESTINIAN TEENS ARE REPORTED KILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JERUSALEM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two Palestinian teen-agers were shot and killed by Israeli troops Monday in the 
occupied West Bank and Gaza Strip, and two others died of wounds suffered in 
earlier clashes, the army and Arab reports said. 
</P>
<P>
Rami Mustafa Tarisi, 15, was fatally shot in the chest in a stone-throwing 
clash in the Bureij refugee camp in the Gaza Strip, according to Arab reports. 
The army said it was checking. 
</P>
<P>
In the West Bank town of Ramallah, 17-year-old Yasser abu Ghosh was fatally 
shot in the head and back by Israeli security forces. 
</P>
