<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: WESTMINSTER; 
</P>
<P>
VIETNAMESE GROUP GETS GRANT FOR SENIOR CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Westminster City Council has awarded the Vietnamese Community of Orange 
County Inc. a grant of $30,000 to build its Asian Senior Acculturation Center. 
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to begin this month and open in early 1990. It will be 
designed for a daily attendance of 70 to 80 senior citizens. The center will be 
at 1618 W. 1st St. in Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
Total project costs are near $1 million, which includes $450,000 from the 
Senior Center Bond Act funds, $270,000 from two grants awarded by Santa Ana and 
more than $100,000 from fund-raising proceeds and donations from foundations, 
private corporations and individuals. 
</P>
<P>
"This is one of our most cherished projects to help our disadvantaged seniors," 
said Mai Cong, president of the board of directors of the Vietnamese community 
group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
