<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ALAMITOS; 
</P>
<P>
ROBBER GETS AWAY WITH CASH FROM S&amp;L 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A robber who displayed a gun under his jacket escaped with an undetermined 
amount of cash Monday from a local savings and loan, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The bandit walked into the Hawthorne Savings &amp; Loan branch in the 3500 
block of Katella Avenue about 11:50 a.m. and handed a teller a note demanding 
money, Los Alamitos Police dispatcher Bill Coleman said. 
</P>
<P>
After taking the money, the man fled through the bank's south door, Coleman 
added. The bandit was described as white, in his 30s, about 5-foot-8 or 
5-foot-10, with curly brown hair and wearing a dark suit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
