<P>
ROBBER'S GUN GOES OFF IN CYSTAL COURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A robber's gun accidentally discharged at the J.W. Robinson Co. department 
store in Costa Mesa's Crystal Court before the thief fled with at least $17,000 
on Monday, authorities said. No one was hurt. 
</P>
<P>
Costa Mesa Police Sgt. James Watson said the lone gunman forced a female 
employee from a credit office to a rear cashier room. After he encountered 
other employees, he took cash estimated at between $17,000 and $25,000, 
stuffing it into a trash can. 
</P>
<P>
"In his excitement," Watson said, the gunman dropped his gun, which went off. 
</P>
