<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND; 
</P>
<P>
BOY HELD AFTER CHASE IN STOLEN CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 12-year-old boy driving a stolen car led sheriff's deputies on a 15-minute 
chase early today that ended in Pasadena when he tried to run over a deputy, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Deputies found a stolen, unloaded AK-47 assault rifle in the car after they 
arrested the 12-year-old El Monte boy, Deputy Pat Hunter said. 
</P>
<P>
Deputies tried to stop the stolen car in Altadena at about 12:45 a.m., Hunter 
said. The boy, however, refused to stop and led deputies on a chase through 
Pasadena and Altadena at speeds of 35 to 65 m.p.h. "After the 15-minute pursuit 
the youth drove the car onto an embankment as he attempted to enter the 
eastbound Foothill Freeway," Hunter said. 
</P>
<P>
As deputies approached the car on foot, the youth suddenly accelerated the 
vehicle at the deputies, Hunter said. One deputy suffered a slight injury to a 
knee as he jumped to avoid being struck. The boy was arrested without further 
incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
