<P>
CARLUCCI WARNS ON PROTECTIONISM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former Defense Secretary Frank C. Carlucci cautioned today against strict 
protectionist legislation to help the declining U.S. defense industry, saying 
the country can't "go it alone" technologically. 
</P>
<P>
"If we protect U.S. industries from foreign competition, we reduce the 
incentive to invest in modern facilities and advanced technologies, and we 
deprive ourselves of access to advances in technology being achieved in foreign 
countries," Carlucci told the Senate Banking, Housing and Urban Affairs 
Committee. 
</P>
<P>
Congress is weighing renewal of the Defense Production Act, which expires Sept. 
30. 
