</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TIJUANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Juan Jose Estrada of Mexico retained his World Boxing Assn. junior 
featherweight title here Monday night with a unanimous 12-round decision over 
Colombian Luis Mendoza. 
</P>
<P>
Estrada was always in control, despite a dangerous opponent who was quick and 
showed that he had a powerful punch. But Estrada was in better physical shape 
and took the fight to the Colombian. 
</P>
<P>
Mendoza landed punches repeatedly to the face of the champion, but the 
difference between them was reflected in the verdict. The three judges all 
scored it 117-112 to Estrada. 
</P>
<P>
This was Estrada's third successful defense of the title he won on May 2, 1988, 
when he beat Bernardo Pinango of Venezuela. 
</P>
